Traditional rulers in Imo state have unanimously adopted the presidential candidate of All Progressives Congress (APC), President Muhammadu Buhari, for second term. The monarchs said that Buhari has done well to deserve another term. The traditional rulers who were more than 600 in attendance and led by their Chairman, HRM Eze Agunwa Ohiri also reserved the chieftaincy title of Omenkeahuruanya (I) of Imo state for the President. A statement by the Chief Press Secretary to Governor Rochas Okorocha, Sam Onwuemeodo, on Wednesday quoted the traditional rulers as making the endorsement in the palace of Eze Imo, His Royal Majesty, Eze Agunwa, when the president paid him a courtesy visit on Tuesday. The monarchs said that the best that can happen to the nation is to vote for President Buhari for another term of four years, stressing that the chieftaincy title is expected to bring the President back to the state for conferment. They urged the president to continue with the fight against corruption, saying that Buhari must be encouraged to succeed. Igbos will vote for Buhari in 2019 - Eze Ohanwe Igbos’ll vote for Buhari in 2019 — Eze Ohanwe S/East traditional rulers endorse Buhari for 2019